The paper proposes a deep learning-based solution for analyzing electronic medical records (EMR) to predict patient outcomes. This involves embedding feature sequences separately by modeling the time-aware distribution and improving multi-head self-attention via cross-head decorrelation to capture inter-dependencies among dynamic features and static baseline information. This work involves machine learning, healthcare, and information retrieval, which are covered by the arXiv CS sub-categories cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.AI, cs.HC, and cs.IR.
